        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down. | Bromley. | Kent. S.E.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>March 20<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>.</date>
                    <salute>My dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>The new title is fixed.<ref target="#foot.f2"/> Many thanks about the clean sheets. I will not forget about the other german publisher.<ref target="#foot.f3"/> With respect to the number of copies I am in that useful frame of mind that when you propose a small number I wish for more &amp; now that you propose 1500 I am frightened so my opinion goes for nothing.<ref target="#foot.f4"/></p>
<p>My dear Sir | yours sincerely | Ch. Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

            
        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The year is established by the relationship between this letter and the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-5448.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from John Murray, 19 March [1867]</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">CD refers to <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_7951.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Variation</hi></ref>; see <ref target="./DCP-LETT-5448.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from John Murray, 19 March [1867]</ref> and n. 2.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3">Murray had agreed to send extra sets of proof-sheets for the German and Russian translations of <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_7951.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Variation</hi></ref>, and had reported that another German publisher was interested in bringing out a German translation of <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_7951.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Variation</hi></ref> (see <ref target="./DCP-LETT-5448.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from John Murray, 19 March [1867]</ref> and n. 5).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f4">See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-5448.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from John Murray, 19 March [1867]</ref> and n. 3.</note>
        </div>        
            
